Credit
Integrating a Borrowing Strategy into Your Financial Plans
	A well-thought-out credit strategy can help you accomplish wide-ranging financial objectives, both today and well into the future.

	Your J.P. Morgan team can help you evaluate both sides of your personal balance sheet to ensure that your assets and liabilities are working well together.





				Enhancing Long-Term Plans






					A well-crafted credit strategy can be an effective complement to your long-range plans. Borrowed capital may also help protect or enhance a long-term investment strategy.

					 



					Credit strategies can allow you to:



							Transfer wealth to future generations or charitable organizations, according to your wishes



							Take advantage of tax efficiencies to help preserve and grow your wealth over time



							Diversify a concentrated stock position to lower portfolio risk without selling assets



							Add leverage to investments to potentially enhance future returns







Gaining a Tactical Advantage


 
 
	Having ready access to credit can help you optimize day-to-day cash flow and avoid selling assets that may appreciate in value or offer more favorable capital gains treatment at a future date.
 
	Having a line of credit in place, you can:


		Take advantage of unexpected opportunities as well as planned investments

		Meet tax obligations and finance large purchases or acquisitions

		Preserve cash for emergencies or other purposes

		Buy a home or vacation property








				Creating Financial Flexibility






					Often, the best credit strategy is one that you put in place ahead of when you may need the funds. In other instances, we can customize a loan to your needs.

					 



					The Capital Advisor on your J.P. Morgan team can help you decide among a range of options:



							Lines of credit secured by marketable securities, including concentrated or restricted stock



							Jumbo mortgages for U.S. properties tailored to address your specific situation, including loans to trusts, LLCs and other special entities



							Structured credit solutions to finance private aircrafts, fine art, life insurance premiums or other illiquid assets






