JPMorgan Trust I - JPMorgan Research Market Neutral Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 6:13 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of JPMorgan Trust I - JPMorgan Research Market Neutral Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
JPMorgan Trust I - JPMorgan Research Market Neutral Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched by J.P. Morgan Investment Management Inc. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It takes long and short positions to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in value stocks of mid-cap and large-cap companies within the market capitalization range of the Russell 1000 and/or Standard & Poor’s 500 Index. It employs market neutral strategy to create its portfolio. The fund employs fundamental analysis focusing on factors like attractive valuation, catalysts that could trigger a rise in a stock’s price, impact on the overa...
JPMorgan Trust I - JPMorgan Research Market Neutral Fund is an open ended equity mutual fund launched by J.P. Morgan Investment Management Inc. The fund invests in the public equity markets of the United States. It takes long and short positions to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in value stocks of mid-cap and large-cap companies within the market capitalization range of the Russell 1000 and/or Standard & Poor’s 500 Index. It employs market neutral strategy to create its portfolio. The fund employs fundamental analysis focusing on factors like attractive valuation, catalysts that could trigger a rise in a stock’s price, impact on the overall risk of the portfolio relative to the benchmark, and temporary mispricing caused by market overreactions to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the BoFA Merrill Lynch 3-Month U.S. Treasury Bill Index and Lipper Alternative Equity Market Neutral Funds Average. The fund employs in-house research to create its portfolio. It was formerly known as JPMorgan Trust I - JPMorgan Market Neutral Fund. JPMorgan Trust I - JPMorgan Research Market Neutral Fund was formed on December 31, 1998 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


270 Park AvenueNew York, NY 10017-2014United StatesFounded in 1998



Phone: 212-648-1999

Fax: 212-648-1790

am.jpmorgan.com/us/en/asset-management/gim/adv/products/d/jpmorgan-research-market-neutral-fund-a-48







